fields.name: Jane Austen
fields.biograpy: Jane Austen was an English novelist known primarily for her six major novels, which interpret, critique, and comment upon the British landed gentry at the end of the 18th century.

fields.name: Charles Dickens
fields.biograpy: Charles John Huffam Dickens was an English writer and social critic. He created some of the world's best-known fictional characters and is regarded by many as the greatest novelist of the Victorian era.

fields.name: Virginia Woolf
fields.biograpy: Adeline Virginia Woolf was an English writer, considered one of the most important modernist 20th-century authors and also a pioneer in the use of stream of consciousness as a narrative device.

fields.name: Gabriel García Márquez
fields.biograpy: Gabriel José de la Concordia García Márquez was a Colombian novelist, short-story writer, screenwriter, and journalist, known affectionately and familiarly as Gabo or Gabito throughout Latin America.

fields.name: Chinua Achebe
fields.biograpy: Chinua Achebe was a Nigerian novelist, poet, professor, and critic. His first novel 'Things Fall Apart' (1958) is considered his magnum opus, and is the most widely read book in modern African literature.
